              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Watch ISO 27001 Annex A 5.1 Policies for Information Security Explained Simply"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "heading": "How to comply",
              "level": 2,
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "To comply with ISO 27001 Annex A 5.1 you are going to implement the ‘how’ to the ‘what’ the control is expecting. In short measure you are going to"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Write an ISO 27001 information security policy"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Supplement that information security policy with topic specific policies"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Ensure your policies are classified and have document mark up"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Have the policies approved by management and have evidence of that happening"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Publish the policies to a place everyone that needs to see them can see them"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Tell those people where those policies are"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Communicate your policies as part of your communication plan and document you did it"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Get people to acknowledge the policies and keep evidence that they have"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Plan to review your policies at least annually or if significant change occurs"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Keep records of your policy review and the changes"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "heading": "What the auditor will check",
              "level": 2,
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The audit is going to check a number of areas for compliance with Annex A 5.1. Lets go through them"
                },
                {
                  "heading": "1. That you can link policy to requirements",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "What this means is that you need to show that your policies are linked"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "to the business strategy, which you recorded and evidenced in the ISO 27001 organisation overview template."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "to the law, regulations and contracts , which you recorded in the ISO 27001 legal register."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "to risks, which you recorded in your ISO 27001 risk register."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "heading": "2. That your policy includes required statements",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "For the main ISO 27001 information security policy there are some required statements that need to be included. You need to"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "define information security and the confidentiality, integrity and availability definition"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "include your information security objectives"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "include principles that will guide on information security activities activities"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "include a commitment to satisfy applicable requirements related to information security"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "have a commitment to continually improving your information security management system"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "assign responsibilities for information security management to defined roles"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "cover how you handle exemptions and exceptions."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "heading": "3. That top management approved the policy",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "The audit will look to see that the main ISO 27001 information security policy and the topic specific policies have been approved and signed off by top management. The level will have been defined in your ISO 27001 Roles and Responsibilities Template document in line with ISO 27001 Annex A 5.2 Roles and Responsibilities"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "heading": "Mistakes People Make",
              "level": 2,
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "In my experience, the top 3 mistakes people make for ISO 27001 Annex A 5.1 are"
                },
                {
                  "heading": "You have no evidence that anything actually happened",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "You need to keep records and minutes of everything. You need a paper trail to show it was done. Make sure you have updated communication plans, minutes of meetings, records of acknowledgement, records of approval. If it isn’t written down it didn’t happen."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "heading": "One or more members of your team haven’t done what they should have done",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Prior to the audit check that all members of the team have done what they should have. Do they know where the policies are? Have they acknowledged them? Did someone join last month and forget to do it? Check!"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "heading": "Your document and version control is wrong",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Keeping your document version control up to date, making sure that version numbers match where used, having a review evidenced in the last 12 months, having documents that have no comments in are all good practices."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "heading": "ISO 27001 Templates",
              "level": 2,
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Implementing ISO 27001 can be a significant undertaking and incur significant ISO 27001 Costs. To streamline the process and potentially save valuable time and resources, consider utilising pre-written ISO 27001 templates. This ISO 27001 Toolkit offers a comprehensive set of resources specifically designed for those seeking to achieve ISO 27001 certification independently. With this toolkit, you can potentially build your Information Security Management System (ISMS) within a week and be ready for certification within 30 days."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "heading": "Changes and Differences to ISO 27002:2013",
              "level": 2,
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "While the 2022 version of ISO 27001 retains many similarities to its predecessor, distinctions emerge:"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Control 5.1 “Information Security Policies” in ISO 27001:2022 consolidates two controls (5.1.1 and 5.1.2) from the 2013 version. While the core principle remains the same – establishing and maintaining an information security policy – the 2022 version provides a more comprehensive and structured approach."
                },
                {
                  "heading": "Key Enhancements in ISO 27001:2022",
                  "level": 3,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Expanded Guidance: Control 5.1 now includes a detailed description of its purpose and expanded implementation guidance."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Attributes Table: The inclusion of an attributes table facilitates easier mapping of controls to industry-specific terminologies."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Enhanced Requirements: The policy requirements are more comprehensive, encompassing:Clear definition of information security.\n\nEstablishment of information security objectives.\n\nCommitment to continuous improvement of the ISMS."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Clear definition of information security."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Establishment of information security objectives."
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Commitment to continuous improvement of the ISMS."
                    },
