                {
                  "text": "Regularly: At least annually, or more frequently if there are significant changes (e.g., new technologies, regulatory updates, security incidents)."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Disciplinary action may be taken, depending on the severity of the violation. Consequences can range from warnings to termination of employment."
                },
                {
                  "text": "Develop standard operating procedures (SOPs) that incorporate security controls.Provide regular training and guidance to employees on how to implement policies in their daily work.Conduct regular audits and assessments to monitor compliance."
